<paragraph id="8B953695207FFFB74DFBFA31FDA7C7C5" blockId="2.[151,639,1416,1730]" pageId="2" pageNumber="122">
This species was placed in “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D16207FFFB74C8BFA32FD97C4D4" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1871" box="[479,590,1469,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amphitasus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEA87207FFFB74C8BFA32FD97C4D4" box="[479,590,1469,1491]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="122">Amphitasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B64207FFFB74DC3FA57FEF8C4EA" author="Lorenz, W." box="[151,289,1496,1517]" pageId="2" pageNumber="122" refId="ref3797" refString="Lorenz, W. 1998. Systematic list of extant ground beetles of the world (Insecta, Coleoptera &quot; Geadephaga &quot;: Trachypachidae and Carabidae incl. Paussinae, Cicindelinae, Rhysodinae). Privately published, W. Lorenz, Tutzing, Germany." type="book" year="1998">Lorenz (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. We have not seen the type (MNHN). However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B64207FFFB74DAEFA7CFEACC70F" author="Bates, H. W." box="[250,373,1523,1544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="122" pagination="77 - 81" refId="ref2920" refString="Bates, H. W. 1871. Notes on Carabidae, and descriptions of new species (No. 7). Entomologist' s Monthly Magazine 8: 77 - 81." type="journal article" year="1871">Bates (1871)</bibRefCitation>
, not Lorenz, is the one who first suggested 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D16207FFFB74C70F982FE5CC724" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" box="[292,389,1549,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anchomenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B95EEA87207FFFB74C70F982FE5CC724" box="[292,389,1549,1571]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="122">A. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belonged in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D16207FFFB74CA9F982FDA1C724" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1871" box="[509,632,1549,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amphithasus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEA87207FFFB74CA9F982FDA1C724" box="[509,632,1549,1571]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="122">Amphithasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as Bates wrote “It is probable that 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D16207FFFB74CB1F9A8FDA6C73A" authority=", Dej." authorityName="Dej." box="[485,639,1575,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anchomenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B95EEA87207FFFB74CB1F9A8FD91C73A" box="[485,584,1575,1597]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="122">A. elegans</emphasis>
, Dej.
</taxonomicName>
(Sp., v, 725) belongs also to the genus.” referring to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D16207FFFB74DC3F9D3FECBC775" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1871" box="[151,274,1628,1650]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amphithasus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEA87207FFFB74DC3F9D3FECBC775" box="[151,274,1628,1650]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="122">Amphithasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus id="54918837207FFFB74C0FF9D2FE77C775" box="[347,430,1629,1650]" pageId="2" pageNumber="122">holotype</typeStatus>
is from Cartagena, 
<collectingCountry id="F33D7605207FFFB74DC3F9F7FF2EC78A" box="[151,247,1656,1677]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="122">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, but it was not found by DHK among lachnophorines in MNHN during his visit in 2016. We suggest it may be among the platynines rather
</paragraph>
